<dl id="n08178j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08178j">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08178j"> 178(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> only heroes armed / bow used very late</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Cuchulain and the rest belonged to the age when metal was scarce, and probably the rank and file had very poor weapons and no defensive armour. The Irish did not use the bow in fighting till very late in their history. <small> Stephen Gwynn, <a name="SGHI" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SGHI"><cite title="source">The History of Ireland</cite></a> (1923) 7</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
